item.description:
TC: Hal Katzman
EVENT: Come walk in the woods around a serene lake located within Kendrick Park reservation on the Newton-Needham line. This undeveloped land borders the Charles River from the Newton area south to Dedham. On this walk, weâ€™ll try to do some further walking within the park. Expect to walk 1.5 miles plus any additional reservation exploring. This walk has been very popular in the past. Bite to eat possible afterwards.
RSVP: Requested to Hal at (singer4hir@hotmail.com) or 617-969-6454 in case of rain cancellation, and so we know to expect you.
MEET: 2 p.m. at Cutler Park parking lot on Kendrick Street near the Leventhal-Sidman JCC, Needham. From Route 128, take exit 19 toward Needham and take the first left at Muzi Ford onto Hunting Road. At first light, take another left onto Kendrick Street and the parking lot will be on the right just after the first light.
COST: money for refreshments afterwards + $5 for non-members
